CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 3 reads: " "Howdy, Senator" - Senator Kennedy received the warmest greeting accorded anyone since the days of F.D.R. and the 1936 campaign. Here he shakes hands with some admirers..."
TitMainTitle: Kennedy-Johnson presidential campaign: John F. Kennedy shaking hands with man standing next to Pennsylvania Governor David L. Lawrence, on platform with press photographer
